com.cubeia.firebase.api.mtt.seating
Class SeatingContainer

java.lang.Object
  com.cubeia.firebase.api.mtt.seating.SeatingContainer

public final class SeatingContainer
extends Object

Represents a seating of a player at a table. Used for telling Firebase to seat a player at a Table. Holds the playerId of the seated player, the tableId of the table where he is seated and the seatId which represents the seat at the table. Additional game specific playerData can be added if the table where the player is being seated needs to know more details. For example, if a player is moved from one table to another, the player's current balance might be attached in the playerData.

Instances of this class have a short life cycle within Firebase and will not be serialized. They are only used for creating a message which will then be sent to the Table (in a SeatPlayersMttAction), after which the instance will be garbage collected.

NOTE. When attaching game specific playerData the class loader will complain (with a ClassNotFoundException) if the class has not been loaded from the top level class loader. The workaround for this is currently to put the jar containing the class under lib/common.
